# Angular Component Rules

- Components should focus on presentation and user interaction.
- Avoid placing connection lifecycle logic directly in components.
- Prefer injecting services for library integration.
- Prefer `ChangeDetectionStrategy.OnPush`.
- Prefer `input()` and `output()` for component inputs and outputs.
- Keep templates readable and simple.
- Avoid large components.
